<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">f1 := (x, y) -&gt; x * (3 - x- 2 * y); </Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">f2 := (x, y) -&gt; y * (2 - x - y);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1876" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">DE1 := diff(x(t), t) = f1(x(t),y(t));</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">DE2 := diff(y(t), t) = f2(x(t),y(t));</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1874" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">DE  := DE1, DE2:</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L181" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="_cstyle15" layout="_pstyle177">Calculate fixed points</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L183" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">sol := solve({f1(x,y)=0, f2(x,y)=0}, {x,y});</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L184" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150">For the stability we need to calculate the Jacobian.  This can be done using a function from the VectorCalculus package without actually loading the entire VectorCalculus package (you don't want that)</Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L189" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">J := VectorCalculus:-Jacobian([f1(x,y), f2(x,y)], [x,y]);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L190" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150">Jacobian for fixed point 4 and its stability</Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1392" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">J4 := subs(sol[4], J);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1394" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">Eigenvalues(J4);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L191" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">evalf(%);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L192" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"> So the fixed point is a saddle node as lambda1&gt;0 and lambda2 &lt; 0</Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
