<Group labelreference="L1642" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle19" layout="_pstyle181">Manipulating solutions from dsolve</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1643" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">Often one would like to be able to manipulate the data obtained from dsolve. This can be done requiring that the numerical data be put into an Array. </Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="Normal">First create an array which specifies when the data must be sampled. </Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1644" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">N:=2500; dt := 0.01;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1647" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">samples := Array(1..N, i -&gt; (i-1)*dt):</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L207" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">sol_arr := dsolve({DE,ic1},[x(t),y(t),z(t)],type=numeric,maxfun=-1,output=samples):</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L208" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150">The returned data is an Array of Arrays. 
</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L209" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">sol_arr;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L210" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="_pstyle155"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150">As can be seen, the data is in the second column, with t,x,y,z respectively. </Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150">Type &quot;? dsolve/numeric&quot; for more information on dsolve's array format</Text-field>
<Text-field style="Text" layout="_pstyle155"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L211" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">soldd:=sol_arr[2,1];</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L212" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">T := soldd[1..N, 1]:</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">X := soldd[1..N, 2]:</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">Y := soldd[1..N, 3]:</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">Z := soldd[1..N, 4]:</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L213" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150">Make a 3D-plot of the lorenz attractor. Click on the image and move the mouse to rotate.      </Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L214" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">l3d := seq([X[i], Y[i], Z[i]], i=1..N):</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1665" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">pointplot3d([l3d], axes=boxed, connect = true, labels=[&quot;x&quot;, &quot;y&quot;, &quot;z&quot;]);</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L216" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle24" layout="_pstyle182">Fractals</Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L217" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150">First we have to generate a fractal object. We'll do this by using a dicrete mapping whose attractor is the so-called Sierpinsky carpet.</Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L218" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">restart; with(plots):</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1678" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">N:=10000;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1684" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150">Define a random integer generator r for numbers [0,1,2]  </Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1683" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">r := rand(3):</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1682" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150">Create a X,Y series</Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1688" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">X := Array(0..N):</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">Y := Array(0..N):</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1694" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">X[0] := 1; Y[0] := 0;</Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L1681" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">for n from 0 to N-1 do</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154"></Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">  dice := r();</Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150"></Text-field>
<Text-field style="_cstyle3" layout="_pstyle150">       Depending on the result of the dice [0, 1, 2] jump to a new point</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">  if( dice = 0) then </Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">    X[n+1] := 0.5 * X[n];</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">    Y[n+1] := 0.5 * Y[n];</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">  else </Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">    if( dice = 1 ) then </Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">       X[n+1] := 0.5 * X[n] + 0.25;</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">       Y[n+1] := 0.5 * Y[n] + 0.50;</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">    else</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">       X[n+1] := 0.5 * X[n] + 0.5;</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">       Y[n+1] := 0.5 * Y[n];</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">    end if;</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">  end if;</Text-field>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="_pstyle154">od:</Text-field>
</Input>
